    <body><div type="letter">
      <p>Brighton Friday Afternoon</p>
      <p>My Dearest Mate. The 75..0..0 is safe. I believe my stay here will have cost very little, which is just as well.--</p>
      <p>I find there is a report that I am going to Jersey for the recovery of my health, so you had best go there straight from Ashley, instead of coming here.--</p>
      <p>The heat today is extreme, so</p>
      <p>that I can scarcely write.--</p>
      <p>1/2 pst 5 o'clock. I was interrupted in the above by the entrance of Dr King-- since which I have been to pay a visit in the Hen's phaeton, &amp; to call also on Miss Fortescue with the Hen, who wished to make her acquaintance.-- The Hen thinks Emily's present game is not to see either her or me. E has not yet returned Mama's card, which I call rude. Mama thinks E's object is to make out that we cut her, which she might</p>
      <p>easily do by suppressing the fact of our repeatedly leaving cards &amp; finding her out of the house. I intend however to baffle her, if this is her plan. I must make haste however, as I find from Aunt Lucy that E means to go to Town. This looks very like keeping out of our way.-- No time for more,</p>
      <p>Ou Birdie A. K.</p>
      <p>The bird is become as strong as a horse!-- and the little bird promises to resist the various modes of destructive kindness which the Education of past ages have devised--</p>
    </div></body>
